<DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
   <title> The align-items Property </title>
   <style type="text/css">
      .container {
         display: flex;
         align-items: flex-start;
         background: blue;
         padding: 5px;
         height: 400px;
      }
      .container > div {
         background: yellow;
         width: 130px;
         line-height: 80px;
         text-align: center;
         margin: 5px;
      }
   </style>
</head>
<body>
   <p> To better demonstrate this, we have to increase the height of the flex container. </p>
   <div class="container">
      <div style="font-size: 20px"> 1 </div>
      <div style="font-size: 40px"> 2 </div>
      <div style="font-size: 60px"> 3 </div>
   </div>
   <p> <b>align-items</b> valid values: </p>
   <ul>
      <li><b>flex-start</b>: aligns flex items to the start of the cross axis </li>
      <li><b>flex-end</b>: aligns flex items to the end of the cross axis </li>
      <li><b>center</b>: aligns flex items to the center (or middle) of the cross axis </li>
      <li><b>stretch</b>: default; stretches flex items to fill the container </li>
      <li><b>baseline</b>: aligns items such as their baselines are aligned </li>
   </ul>
</body>
</html>